@yagebu I know this and checked the syntax files, but:
  - It does not (I think) explain why the problem builds up over time. Also, the scrolling is just a part of the problem, although the most visible.
  - If that's the problem, switching the filetype to 'txt' (or anything with little to no syntax highlighting, and no folding) should solve the problem "dynamically", but the only thing that does that (among what I tested) was `set norelativenumber`

@justinmk,

I have not, I have primarily use the Neovim stable releases (0.3.1 for now).

Just knowing that the Vim patch has already been merged is good enough, that patch works and it will be available in the next Neovim release which is excellent news.
